    "narrative": "The centerpiece of our offense today is clearly **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who commands an elite 80.96 score against Arrighetti. With a favorable matchup against a starter carrying a 5.10 xERA and a high-probability SB environment due to the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** is our primary anchor. Following him, **Will Smith** (74.95) and **Lawrence Butler** (65.53) offer the highest upside. **Will Smith** benefits immensely from a soft matchup against Quintana, while **Lawrence Butler** leverages his strong platoon advantage to overcome a lower batting order slot, providing a crucial power-speed profile we prioritize in this 5x5 format.\n\nNavigating the marginal tier, **Bryson Stott** (64.42) remains a start despite an elite-level hold pitcher, as his high dynamic platoon edge keeps him firmly in the \"Strong\" category. Conversely, **Daulton Varsho** stands as our most significant bench decision; he failed to clear the 40.0 floor threshold (37.59) primarily due to a challenging matchup against Detmers and a bottom-third batting order placement. While **Cal Raleigh** (50.40) and **Yainer Diaz** (52.02) are technically \"Marginal\" plays, they retain their spots in the lineup to hedge against the volatility of our other mid-tier assets. We are monitoring **Tyler Freeman** closely; while his matchup against Wrobleski is tough (2.89 xERA), his 85% SB potential in this specific matchup scenario provides the necessary categorical scarcity to justify the start over deeper bench options like **Gavin Sheets** or **Drew Gilbert**. \n\nRisks today are concentrated in the mid-range of our lineup. **Gleyber Torres** (41.31) and **Masyn Winn** (45.10) are barely clinging to their starting roles; any further negative movement in their projected environment could see them swapped for fresher bench legs in future rotations. Ensure **Luis Arraez**, **Brendan Donovan**, and **Jung Hoo Lee** remain on standby should late-inning defensive substitutions or unforeseen lineup shifts impact the availability of **Jeremiah Jackson** or **Taylor Ward**, as both occupy the lower-end \"Strong\" tier and carry minimal margin for error against Lugo.",
